By: Sri Sankarâchârya
Commentary: Realization itself is not within reach of the volitive faculties,
 it being rather a matter of ripeness and maturity -- volition of course
 being presupposed.
---
The Knowledge of one’s identity with the pure Self that negates the (wrong)
notion of the identity of the body and the Self sets a man free even against
his will when it becomes as firm as the belief of the man that he is a
human being.
